scree.Rd

Pre-processing to generate scagnostic measures

scree(x, y, binner = NULL, ...)

Arguments

x, y

numeric vectors
binner

an optional function that bins the x and y vectors prior to triangulation
...

other args

Value

An object of class "scree" that consists of three elements: - `del`: the Delauney-Vornoi tesselation from [alphahull::delvor()] - `weights`: the lengths of each edge in the Delauney triangulation - `alpha`: the radius or `alpha` value that will be used to generate the alphahull

Examples


x <- runif(100)
y <- runif(100)
scree(x,y)
